      {
        "id": 2566853,
        "name": "Scott Tallman",
        "username": "Scott_Tallman",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/scott_tallman/{size}/1825_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-01-25T17:53:34.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>John Thomas has email now and is responsive, so I\u2019d email him to see what he says. I was thinking of asking for a visit when I go down in March.</p>\n<p>As for Cameron, I was lucky enough to be invited by a fellow Berserker to the pre-Thanksgiving open house a few years ago. But my understanding is John generally does not allow consumer visits. But I\u2019d email/call to see what is possible.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://www.cameronwines.com/contact-us/\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://www.cameronwines.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">cameronwines.com</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    \n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.cameronwines.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Cameron Winery - Pinot Noir and Chardonnay   Contact Us</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Since 1984, Cameron Winery has fanatically produced sustainably farmed, non-irrigated pinot noir, chardonnay and pinot bianco from the Red Hills of Dundee, Oregon</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
